# Obsidian Docs — Source of Truth

The Obsidian vault at **`docs/PrisonEscape/`** is the **canonical source of truth** for game design, prison layout, features, escape routes, and project direction.

## Before making design or layout decisions

1. Read relevant notes in `docs/PrisonEscape/` first (especially `Prison Escape.md` and linked notes/canvas).
2. If Unity code, scenes, or `Assets/Docs/` conflict with Obsidian, **Obsidian wins** unless the user explicitly overrides in chat.
3. When implementing prison layout, cells, rooms, corridors, or escape paths, match the Obsidian diagram and written specs.

## Hierarchy

| Source | Role |
|--------|------|
| `docs/PrisonEscape/` | **Primary** — design, layout, features, devlog |
| `Assets/Docs/` | Secondary — technical docs; must not contradict Obsidian |
| Code / scenes | Implementation of Obsidian specs |

## When updating design

- Update Obsidian notes first (or together with code), then align Unity assets.
- After every work session, also update the **devlog** (`Prison Escape Devlog Dashboard.md`) and run the full checklist in **development-workflow** (`.cursor/rules/development-workflow.mdc`).
- If you change layout or features in Unity, update the vault note — do not only remind the user.

## Vault location

- Vault root: `docs/PrisonEscape/`
- Main design note: `docs/PrisonEscape/Prison Escape.md`
